<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>New idea for running battles</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Soul">Soul</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 12:30 a.m. 13/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> New idea for running battles<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR></STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>Well first of all I really hate people fighting at the edge of a zone with no risk at all. If the fight goes well, fine, else zoning.

<P>In my opinion everybody who was under attack the last 30 sec or is followed by an attacking monster and is fleeing the battle through zoning should have a 50% chance of loosing 1 to 5 skill points of a random skill. That's both for PvP and PvE.
<P>There is no need for loosing exp. points. If you run often you maybe dont loose a level, but what good is a fighter with just average for his lvl in offense or defense cause of running battles all the time?
<BR>Sure you might loose nothing or just some sense direction skill points, but if you run often ...
<P>If you see your offense skill raise the tenth time to the same level you might try fighting till the end next time.
<P>Soul
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
